obo:ECO_0007719  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_1492  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: In this study, Nirenberg et al. showed that VMAT2 is present in dense core vesicles and to a lesser extent in synaptic vesicles by electron microcopy.\n\n22/11/2017 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: In brief,\ntwelve adult, male Sprague-Dawley rats (250-400 g) were\nanesthetized with sodium pentobarbital and perfused through\nthe ascending aorta with 50 ml of 3.75% (vol/vol) acrolein in\n0.1 M phosphate buffer (PB) followed by 250 ml of 2%\n(wt/vol) paraformaldehyde. Sections (30-40 ,m) were cut on\na vibratome, incubated in 1% sodium borohydride, cryoprotected,\nand freeze-thawed as described (11)." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099066 replaced by GO:0099012" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1542-3498" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0808-7003" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3898-5197" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1492" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

